## Database Wrapper (CRITICAL)
Appwrite SDK wrapped in Supabase-compatible API in shared/src/auth/supabase.ts
- getSupabase() returns chainable query builder
- getAccount() returns Appwrite Account instance
- Usage: db().from('collection').select('*').eq('field', value)
- Insert: db().from('collection').insert({ ... })
- Update: db().from('collection').update({ ... }).eq('id', docId)
- Delete: db().from('collection').delete().eq('id', docId)
- Single: .maybeSingle() returns { data: row | null }
- Field 'id' auto-maps to '$id' in Appwrite
- JSON fields (tags, skills, images, packages) stored as strings, auto-parsed on read
- Always add fallback: Array.isArray(x) ? x : JSON.parse(x)

## Collections (13 total)

### fl_profiles — user profiles
user_id(100,req), username(100,req), name(200,req), avatar(500), title(200), bio(2000), location(100), skills(1000,JSON), role(20: freelancer/client/admin/moderator), level(20: new/verified/pro), rating(float), review_count(int), orders_completed(int), response_time(50), is_online(bool), member_since(50), success_rate(int), balance(int)

### fl_gigs — services/kworks
title(300,req), description(5000), short_description(500), image(500), images(2000,JSON), freelancer_id(100,req), freelancer_name(200), freelancer_username(100), rating(float), review_count(int), orders_count(int), tags(500,JSON), category(100), category_slug(100), is_featured(bool), status(20: pending/active/paused/rejected/deleted), package_economy(1000,JSON), package_standard(1000,JSON), package_premium(1000,JSON), rejection_reason(300), moderated_by(50), moderated_at(30)
NOTE: freelancer_avatar DELETED — use enrichGigAvatars() from fl_profiles

### fl_orders
gig_id(100,req), gig_title(300), buyer_id(100,req), client_id(100,req,=buyer_id), seller_id(100,req), seller_name(200), seller_avatar(500), package_type(20), price(int,req), status(30: new/in_progress/delivered/completed/cancelled/revision), requirements(2000), delivery_days(int), delivered_at(50), completed_at(50)

### fl_reviews
gig_id(100,req), order_id(100), author_id(100,req), author_name(200), author_avatar(500), rating(int,req), text(2000), reply(2000)

### fl_categories
slug(100,req), name(200,req), icon(50), description(500), gig_count(int,NOT USED), sort_order(int)

### fl_favorites — user_id(100,req), gig_id(100,req)
### fl_conversations — participant_ids(500,req,JSON), participant_names(500,JSON), participant_avatars(1000,JSON), order_id(100), last_message(500), last_message_at(50)
### fl_messages — conversation_id(100,req), sender_id(100,req), content(5000,req), type(20), read(bool)
### fl_tickets — user_id, user_name, user_email, subject(300), category(50), status(20), priority(20), related_id(100), assigned_to(100), closed_at(50)
### fl_ticket_messages — ticket_id, sender_id, sender_name, message(5000), is_admin(bool)
### fl_projects — user_id(100,req), user_name(200), user_avatar(300), title(300,req), description(3000), category(100), status(20), budget_from(int), budget_to(int), deadline_days(int), responses_count(int)
### fl_portfolio — user_id(100,req), image(500), title(200,req), description(500), link(300), tags(500,JSON)
### fl_gig_extras — gig_id(100,req), title(200,req), description(500), price(int), delivery_days_add(int), sort_order(int)

## Key Files
- src/lib/freelance-db.ts — ALL database functions (CRUD for gigs, orders, reviews, profiles, chat, favorites)
- src/lib/admin-api.ts — Admin/moderator functions + role checks (ADMIN_EMAILS, MODERATOR_EMAILS)
- src/lib/email.ts — Email notifications via Resend
- src/lib/upload.ts — Appwrite Storage file uploads
- src/hooks/useData.ts — React data hooks
- src/types/index.ts — TypeScript interfaces
- shared/src/auth/supabase.ts — DB wrapper (READ ONLY, submodule)
- shared/src/components/Header.tsx — Shared header (READ ONLY, submodule)

## Admin Roles
- ADMIN_EMAILS in admin-api.ts = full access to all admin pages
- MODERATOR_EMAILS = limited access (gigs moderation, users, reviews, tickets, chat)
- AdminLayout checks getAdminRole() and filters nav items

## Key Patterns
- Gigs go through moderation: createGig() sets status='pending', admin approves to 'active'
- enrichGigAvatars() loads freelancer avatars+levels from fl_profiles (MUST call after mapGig)
- AI features (AIGigAnalyzer, AIMatching) call Claude API directly from browser
- All JSON stored as strings, parsed on read by wrapper or manually
- Categories gig_count is calculated dynamically, NOT from DB field

